==English==
===Etymology===
Egyptian ''‘nkh'' "[[life]]"

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æŋk|-æŋk]]

===Noun===
'''ankh''' (''plural'' '''[[ankhs]]''')

#A [[cross]] shaped like a T with a loop at the top, the Egyptian [[hieroglyph]] representing the word "life" and often used as an [[amulet]] or charm for this concept. Also known as an [[ansate cross]].

